<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14046">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b
        >NOTE: Scouts should obey all local fishing regulations and property
        laws.</b
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14101">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Fishing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9543">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9543 mb-requirement-id-9544">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in fishing activities, and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DlReuRpGOtk?si=pPb6SVkfygAeiKvw"
          target="_blank"
          >Fishing - Be Aware Of These Fishing Hazards (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://anglersadvantageguideservice.com/why-is-fishing-dangerous-dont-overlook-these-risks/"
          target="_blank"
          >Why is Fishing Dangerous? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9543 mb-requirement-id-9545">
        (b) Discuss the prevention of and treatment for the following health
        concerns that could occur while fishing: cuts and scratches, puncture
        wounds, insect bites, hypothermia, dehydration, heat exhaustion,
        heatstroke, and sunburn. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0jp5FgLmKtk?si=JoP0J-4mQLgepwth"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Treat Cuts and Bruises (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AmT3T_9Guq0" target="_blank"
          >Removing a Fishhook (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YkUW3pquCF4?si=9ucB7jWL1cgIaHFo"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Treat an Insect Bite or Sting | First Aid Training (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=my6JB41apTw" target="_blank"
          >Hypothermia (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KahsIEbFROI" target="_blank"
          >What is Dehydration? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8gn3DEYOPuE" target="_blank"
          >Heat Exhaustion vs Heat Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-KzTvagnpfU" target="_blank"
          >Sunburn (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9543 mb-requirement-id-9546">
        (c) Explain how to remove a barbed hook that is lodged in someone's arm.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/52GLMQp52qg?si=lGfrvAY2RR2LBCO7"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Remove a Hook (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9543 mb-requirement-id-9547">
        (d) Name and explain five safety practices you should always follow
        while fishing. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/mRQ0HHA3KAo?si=2bj_q6MXIj1KvTqX"
          target="_blank"
          >Fishing Safety Tips (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9552">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Discuss the differences between two types of fishing outfits. Point out
      and identify the parts of several types of rods and reels. Explain how and
      when each would be used. Review with your counselor how to care for this
      equipment. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/C7CWIywYmxk?si=RaRV3MXTIuB5dEf0" target="_blank"
        >Types of Fishing Reels and How to Use Them for Beginners - Spinning vs.
        Spincast vs. Baitcasting (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/E49ZEmiLEPo?si=nEQKsinBVH62ArCc" target="_blank"
        >Cane Pole Fishing (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9553">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Demonstrate the proper use of two different types of fishing equipment.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/cHxF6aZSrIw" target="_blank"
        >How to Cast and Use a Spincast Push Button Rod and Reel - Fishing Reels
        for Beginners (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mZSIvpKVA4c" target="_blank"
        >Fishing 101 Made Easy with Simple Spinning Reel Casting (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/n6XApOOpfA8" target="_blank"
        >How to Use a Baitcaster For Beginners! (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9554">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Demonstrate how to tie the following knots: improved clinch knot, Palomar
      knot, uni knot, uni to uni knot, and arbor knot. Explain how and when each
      knot is used. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://www.animatedknots.com/improved-clinch-knot"
        target="_blank"
        >Improved Clinch Knot (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.animatedknots.com/palomar-knot" target="_blank"
        >Palomar Knot (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.animatedknots.com/uni-knot" target="_blank"
        >Uni Knot (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.wired2fish.com/fishing-knots/how-to-tie-a-double-uni-knot?"
        target="_blank"
        >Uni-to-Uni / Double Uni Knot (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.animatedknots.com/arbor-knot" target="_blank"
        >Arbor Knot (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.animatedknots.com/" target="_blank"
        >Animated Knots (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9555">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Name and identify five basic artificial lures and five natural baits and
      explain how to fish with them. Explain why baitfish are not to be
      released. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://fishingbooker.com/blog/most-common-types-of-fishing-lures-all-you-need-to-know/"
        target="_blank"
        >Most Common Types of Fishing Lures (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/SamrdgVjpQk?si=ePU9bupYp0gi6Jvp" target="_blank"
        >Fishing Lures for Beginners (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://sportfishingbuddy.com/fishing-lure-types-chart/"
        target="_blank"
        >What Are the Different Types Of Fishing Lures? (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://farmerandthefishnyc.com/why-are-bait-fish-not-to-be-released/"
        target="_blank"
        >Why Shouldn't Bait Fish Be Released Back Into the Water? (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nmOdusje6tY" target="_blank"
        >Motivations and Risks of Illegal Baitfish Release (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9548">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9548 mb-requirement-id-9549">
        (a) Explain the importance of practicing Leave No Trace Seven Principles
        and the Outdoor Code. Discuss the positive effects of Leave No Trace
        Seven Principle and the Outdoor Code on fishing resources. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://lnt.org/why/7-principles/" target="_blank"
          >7 Principles of LNT (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://vimeo.com/1115216743/63b20c0b33?share=copy"
          target="_blank"
          >LNT Basics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9548 mb-requirement-id-9550">
        (b) Discuss the meaning and importance of catch and release. Describe
        how to properly release a fish safely to the water. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TzNjYoRpvb0?si=aHLXxtxmVecGaQ-D"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Safely Handle Fish for Catch &amp; Release Fishing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SMGO50R_lrA" target="_blank"
          >Ethical Catch and Release Fishing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9556">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Obtain and review the regulations affecting gamefishing where you live.
      Explain why they were adopted and what is accomplished by following them.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://fishpiers.com/fishing-license-requirements-by-state-all-50-states/"
        target="_blank"
        >Fishing Licenses, Rules, Regulations (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9557">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Explain what good outdoor sportsmanlike behavior is and how it relates to
      anglers. Tell how the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code
      relate to a fishing sports enthusiast, including the aspects of littering,
      trespassing, courteous behavior, and obeying fishing regulations. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/54ImytCqbzI?si=hueVbET92MOl-dIg" target="_blank"
        >Understanding Basic Fishing Rules and Etiquette (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9558">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Catch one fish and identify it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://freeappsforme.com/fish-identification-apps/"
        target="_blank"
        >Fish Identification Apps (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.fishbase.us/" target="_blank"
        >FishBase Identification (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mZ4M-AP6-iQ" target="_blank"
        >How to Identify Common Freshwater Fish (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9551">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10 </span>
      If regulations and health concerns permit, clean and cook a fish you have
      caught. If you are unable to catch a fish for eating, acquire a fish,
      clean the fish you acquired, and cook the fish you acquired. <br /><b
        >Note:</b
      >
      It is not required that you eat the fish. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uBDYqh8p2fU?si=M9GBz5gWCTISdC5k" target="_blank"
        >How to Clean and Care for Your Catch (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/hca5xiZbulY?feature=share"
        target="_blank"
        >How to Fillet a Fish (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/u19fJ10kAVo?feature=share"
        target="_blank"
        >How to Clean a Fish Before Cooking (short video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/BSQhEjSalwk" target="_blank"
        >How to Cook a Fish (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Tgv7tCx2NsA?si=NwsJpJx4rYU3qDOX" target="_blank"
        >5 Easy Ways to Cook Fish (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
